{
  "stem": "20711.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after we were really becoming pretty well off, no more financial trouble, my mother left us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She divorced my father, and she married this young man, Mayer Laszlo.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after that, he keep on working with the cars, but by that time, he had a taxi company.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He owed a beautiful service garage in Budapest, and he was one of the wealthiest men in the country.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for very, very long time that we didn't know, but he was also smuggling people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The taxis not only did a little taxiing during the day, but they also smuggled people out of the country through the Austrian border.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He had contact, and everybody was paid on the way, including the Russian guards.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And for good amount of money, he took a lot of Jewish people through the border, who was illegally emigrating to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I didn't know that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I had a big mouth as a kid, and it was always the major concern of my parents, try to keep everything away from me because sooner or later, it is not going to be a secret.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I didn't know that, just after everything was over.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And sadly, toward the end, one of his chauffeur got caught at the border smuggling somebody, and he was brought back and taken to a very infamous police station, where many, many people got beaten to death.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he got a-- a message-- my stepfather got a message.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "His man is in that police station.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He knew sooner or later they will beat it out of him, who is the head of this organization, and he will be picked up.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So over night, he had to disappear, with my mother and his newborn little daughter, who was only six months old, behind.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
